race.comment: It's hard to knock the form of BALANCE THE BOOKS (16) who has strung three wins together on the bounce to start the career and looks the runner in this field with the most upside. Can continue the picket fence. SER JOH (6) returned to the winners' stall at Doomben last time out and will have taken some confidence from that victory. Is a two-time winner over this track and trip and can go very close again. CASPERNOVA (2) loves this track and trip with two wins and two seconds from five attempts. Doesn't know how to run a bad race and has to be included in calculations. TOWN CRIER (8) rounds out the selections.
